title: For Sale:  Browning FN Herstal 1969 BAR
postcontent: BAR Circa 1969Browning FN HerstalDecades ago, Browning partnered with FN Herstal out of Belgium to begin a long relationship of co-development and manufacturing some of the finest firearms in history from the iconic .50 caliber machine gun utilized by the military known as the "Ma Duece" to the excellent pack rifles safari guides still count on today. Among these was the Browning Automatic Rifle (BAR) which was a finely tuned hunting machine of near-perfect balance and unparalleled accuracy never really seen before in a semi automatic rifle. Today, the BAR is still manufactured by Browning and Miroku out of Japan and even FN Herstal has begun manufacturing their own version of the BAR. Finding a BAR that still carries the branding of Browning and FN Herstal is beyond rare. This particular firearm came off the line in Belgium in 1969 and comes with a Bushnell optic from the same time period. This rifle is in good condition and is chambered in 7mm Remington Magnum making it ideal for big game hunting anywhere in North America and beyond! This is an extremely rare find for a truly serious collector.
